== Roasted Carrots ==

Adjust rack to top position and preheat oven to 425 degrees. Wash and dry produce.

Trim, peel, and cut @carrots{9%ounce} into sticks (like fries; ours were 3 inches long
and 1/3 inch thick). Toss on a #baking sheet{} with a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp},
@harissa powder{1/4%tsp}, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}.

> For easy cleanup, line your baking sheet with foil or parchment paper.

Roast on top rack, tossing halfway through, until browned and tender,
~{15-20%minutes}.

== Bulgur ==

Meanwhile, in a #small pot{}, combine @bulgur wheat{1/2%cup}, 
@veggie stock concentrate{2}, @garlic powder{1/2%tsp}, @water{1%cup}, 
a big pinch of @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Bring to a boil, then reduce
heat to low. Simmer, covered, until water has absorbed and bulgur is tender,
~{12-15%minutes}.

Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

== Prep ==

While bulgur cooks, finely chop @cilantro{1/4%ounce}. Zest and quarter
@lemon{1}. Trim and quarter @zucchini{1} lengthwise; cut crosswise into
1/2-inch-thick pieces. Halve @grape tomatoes{4%ounce} crosswise. Roughly chop
@pistachios{1/2%ounce}.

== Chermoula ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine cilantro, @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp}, a squeeze of
lemon juice, @chili flakes{1%tsp} to taste, and as much remaining
@garlic powder{1/2%tsp} as you like. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Creamy Lemon Sauce ==

In a separate small bowl, combine @sour cream{3%tbsp} and a big pinch of
lemon zest. Add @water{} 1 tsp at a time until sauce reaches a drizzling
consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

== Salmon ==

Pat @skin-on salmon{10%ounce} dry with paper towels; season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably
nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add salmon (skin sides down). Cook until
skin is crisp and fish is almost cooked through, ~{5-7%minutes}, then flip and
cook until cooked through, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a
#plate{}. Wipe out pan.

> Salmon is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.

== Veggies ==

Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over
medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring, until lightly browned,
~{4-6%minutes}.

Add tomatoes, @Tunisian spice blend{1/2%tsp}, and a pinch of @salt{pinch}; cook
until tomatoes are slightly softened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}. Turn off heat.

> Use pan used for salmon here.

== Bulgur Bowl ==

Drain any excess water from bulgur if necessary; fluff with a #fork{}. Stir in
@dried apricots{1%ounce} and @butter{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{} to taste.

Divide bulgur between #bowls{} and top with roasted carrots and veggies. Top
with pistachios. Drizzle with chermoula and lemon sauce. Sprinkle with any
remaining chili flakes to taste. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges on the
side.